le> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulorileibard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LorileiBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/12/02 9:34:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: =\</span><hr size=1> Yes, they added another step to the cleric epic, and they have also pretty much turned it into the likes of a VSR race (first in force).<br><br>However, what they have removed is the need for an entire guild to rotate through the mind-numbing 24/7 camp in SolB.  If you think that was easy on a guild, you are incorrect.  I have been through that grueling camp for 6 clerics.  The stress of staying on line, camping it through the wee hours of the morning, defending it from poachers during the normal work day, fighting the FG respawn when key members of the party have fallen asleep, fighting the boredom between FG respawns, when there is a *single* monk claiming ALL of the LDC's and bitching to high heaven if you take just one LDC, not to mention after the third day of the camp that some guildies notice that other guildies have only stopped in to SolB for an entirety of 2 hours, if that, and resentment begins...<br><br>Yah, individual clerics have now gotten a bit screwed, since they now have a smaller camp mob and a large race mob, but there has been a huge burden removed from that cleric's guild. All they have to do is be ready to race over when the cleric camping SF RF sees him pop.  Or, the cleric in SF needs to have the timing down on the SF RF so that the guild can gather forces about an hour ahead of expected pop to off the final mob.<br><br>(prolly not what you wanted to hear, though)<br>Lori<br><br> <p><TABLE style=filter:glow(color=green, strength=#+10)><font size=2><font color=white>Lorilei Warsong, 60 Virtuoso, Silent Re