27:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ulorileibard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LorileiBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(2/12/02 1:58:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: =\</span><hr size=1> *Any* trigger mob can be spawned and off'ed for the non-epic loot.  There is a guild which has happily been spawning and off'ing bard trak for its single non-guts drop.  Sometimes they have given the guts to a needy bard, but word has it that the guts have also rotted.  VERY frustrating to hear that news!  <br><br>It's tough to hear that a bard who doesn't have both scales yet, somehow has the trak guts.  It's tough to see that they guts are on sale for MQ (although at least one person offered them for an EXTREMELY reasonable price).  It SUCKS to hear that the guts rotted.  So I sympathize with what you are saying, since, no doubt, the cleric epic is headed in this direction. (cept it can't be MQ'd, so needy clerics would have to be there at the time of the slaying)<br><br>However, no matter that the clerics may prefer to have it the old way, about the cleric's GUILD, who had to bear the burden of the camp?  Guaranteed, they are MUCH better off.  <br><br>If you argue otherwise, you must never have sat through an RF camp.  To do an RF camp literally meant putting the entire guild on hold from other raids/things (and even from RL stuff) for 1-4 days, and sometimes longer.  Everyone is needed to pitch in to do long shifts, cover late hours, and even take off work or lose sleep to hold the camp.<br><br>Plus there is the added bonus of no longer worrying about hosting a Naggy raid (esp if Naggy spawned in the *middle* of your RF camp...).  Many RF-ready guilds (who could handle Chardok king) have members who are too high lvl to participate in Naggy raids, and don't enough twinks to be able to pull one of.  You ever run a public Naggy raid?<br><br>(btw, FG respawn time is 6 hours 40 min, and the old RF could actually take up to 80 hours to spawn, provided there wasn't a patch, or Naggy didn't pop on top of him and kill him, or the zone didn't go down for whatever lame reason...) <p><TABLE style=filter:glow(color=green, strength=#+10)><font size=2><font color=white>Lorilei Warsong, 60 Virtuoso, Silent Resurgence</TABLE></font><TABLE style=filter:glow(color=blue, strength=#+10)<font size=2><fontcolor=white>blithely littering the area with little blue floaty notes</TABLE></font><TABLE style=filter:glow(color=green, strength=#+10)><font size=2><font color=white>...and when you get the choice to sit it out or dance,</TABLE></font><TABLE style=filter:glow(color=green, strength=#+10)><font size=2><font color=white>I hope you dance! </TABLE></font></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showPrevMessage?topicID=426.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showNextMessage?topicID=426.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=426.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/AddReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.emailToFriend?topicID=426.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.threadControl?topicID=426.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.c